
[1]hospitable

   HOS'PITABLE, a. [L. hospitalis, from hospes, a guest.]

   1. Receiving and entertaining strangers,with kindness and without
   reward; kind to strangers and guests; disposed to treat guests with
   generous kindness; as a hospitable man.

   2. Proceeding from or indicating kindness to guests; manifesting
   generosity; as a hospitable table; hospitable rites.

   3. Inviting to strangers; offering kind reception; indicating
   hospitality.

   To where yon taper cheers the vale,

   With hospitable ray.
